{"version":1,"entries":{"person_2138291_translations":{"at":1773688718950,"data":{"id":2138291,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"스즈키 료타","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Ryota Suzuki (鈴木 崚汰, Suzuki Ryōta, December 22, 1998) is a Japanese voice actor was born in Nagoya, Aichi and raised in Chiba. He is affiliated with TMS Music. He graduated from the Nihon Narēshon Engi Kenkyū-jo (NichiNare). He was formerly affiliated with Vims agency until March 31, 2023.","name":"Ryota Suzuki","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IN","iso_639_1":"hi","name":"हिन्दी","english_name":"Hindi","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"鈴木崚汰是日本的男性聲優。出生於愛知縣，成長於千葉縣，畢業於日本播音演技研究所，所屬公司為 TMS MUSIC。","name":"鈴木崚汰","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"Ryota Suzuki (鈴木 崚汰, Suzuki Ryōta, nacido el 22 de diciembre de 1998) es un actor de voz japonés. Graduado de la Nihon Narēshon Engi Kenkyū-jo (NichiNare). Pertenece a TMS Music. Nació en la ciudad de Nagoya, prefectura de Aichi, y se crio en la prefectura de Chiba. Estuvo afiliado a la agencia Vims hasta el 31 de marzo de 2023.","name":"Ryota Suzuki","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"鈴木崚汰","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"TH","iso_639_1":"th","name":"ภาษาไทย","english_name":"Thai","data":{"biography":"","name":"เรียวตะ ซูซูกิ","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"铃木崚汰是日本的男性声优。出生于爱知县，成长于千叶县，毕业于日本播音演技研究所，所属公司为TMS MUSIC。","name":"铃木崚汰","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ryota Suzuki","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Rjóta Suzuki","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ryota Suzuki","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"Ryōta Suzuki est un doubleur japonais. Il est affilié à TMS Music. Il est surtout connu comme la voix de Yū Ishigami dans Kaguya-sama : Love Is War. Wikipédia","name":"Ryōta Suzuki","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IT","iso_639_1":"it","name":"Italiano","english_name":"Italian","data":{"biography":"Ryōta Suzuki (鈴木 崚汰, Suzuki Ryōta) è un doppiatore giapponese nato il 22 dicembre 1998 a Nagoya, Aichi e cresciuto a Chiba. È affiliato alla TMS Music. Si è diplomato al Nihon Narēshon Engi Kenkyū-jo (NichiNare). È stato affiliato all'agenzia Vims fino al 31 marzo 2023.","name":"Ryota Suzuki","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"UA","iso_639_1":"uk","name":"Український","english_name":"Ukrainian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Рьота Судзукі","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"鈴木崚汰是日本的男性聲優。出生於愛知縣，成長於千葉縣，畢業於日本播音演技研究所，所屬公司為 TMS MUSIC。","name":"鈴木崚汰","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Рёта Судзуки","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IR","iso_639_1":"fa","name":"فارسی","english_name":"Persian","data":{"biography":"","name":"ریوتا سوزوکی","primary":false}}]}},"person_52601_translations":{"at":1773688719951,"data":{"id":52601,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Sean Patrick Hayes (born June 26, 1970) is an American actor, comedian, and producer. Known for his performances on stage and screen, he gained acclaim for his role as Jack McFarland on the NBC sitcom Will & Grace, for which he won a Primetime Emmy Award and four Screen Actors Guild Awards. He has also received nominations for six Golden Globe Awards and two Tony Awards, winning one.\n\nHe also runs a television production company called Hazy Mills Productions, which produces shows such as Grimm, Hot in Cleveland, The Soul Man, and Hollywood Game Night. He portrayed Jerry Lewis in the CBS film Martin and Lewis (2002). He is known for his appearances in films such as Billy's Hollywood Screen Kiss (1998), Cats & Dogs (2001), Pieces of April (2003), The Cat in the Hat (2003), Win a Date with Tad Hamilton! (2004), The Bucket List (2007), Igor (2008), The Three Stooges (2012), Monsters University (2013), and Am I OK? (2022). Since July 2020, he has co-hosted the comedy podcast SmartLess alongside Jason Bateman and Will Arnett.\n\nHayes made his Broadway debut playing Chuck Baxter in the musical revival Promises, Promises in 2010, for which he was nominated for the Tony Award for Best Leading Actor in a Musical. He portrayed God in the comedy An Act of God from 2015 to 2016. Oscar Levant in the Doug Wright play Good Night, Oscar in 2022, the latter of which earned him the Tony Award for Best Leading Actor in a Play. He hosted the 64th Tony Awards in 2010, for which he was awarded a Primetime Emmy Award.\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article Sean Hayes, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.","name":"Sean Hayes","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"SA","iso_639_1":"ar","name":"العربية","english_name":"Arabic","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"肖恩·海耶斯（Sean Hayes，1970年6月26日-），美国演员、喜剧演员。","name":"肖恩·海耶斯","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","n